net.sf.opengroove.client
Enum Symbol

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<Symbol>
      net.sf.opengroove.client.Symbol
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Symbol>
public enum Symbol
extends Enum<Symbol>

A bunch of symbols that I've found that I think could be used in portions of OpenGroove. the toString() method on each symbol returns a string with the symbol itself, so you can just embed symbol enum constants directly within strings. The string returned from toString() is guaranteed to only have one symbol as encoded in UTF-8, although there is no guarantee that it will use only one byte. In fact, almost all of the symbols here use two or more bytes when encoded with UTF-8.

Author:
Alexander Boyd
